; NSF PROFILE.TCPIP -- SYS2.PARMLIB(NSFPRM0) for the M1 CTCI bring-up.
;
; Read at "S NSF" through the PROFILE DD (see samplib/NSF). The syntax is
; PROFILE.TCPIP-compatible where IBM defines it; the NSF* statements are NSF
; extensions. Full grammar + validation: docs/Architecture-Specification.md ch.14.
;
; All-or-nothing: any error rejects startup with an NSF7xxE message and the
; 1-based line number -- there is no partial configuration.
;
; NOTE: the running STC (nsfstc.c) validates this config but does NOT itself
; open a device -- it checks LINK->DEVICE / HOME->LINK referential integrity by
; NAME, so "S NSF" proves the CUU parses, not that the channel opens. The CUU
; pair is driven by test/mvs/tstctcm.c part 2, built -DNSFCTCI_CUU=0x0500
; (issue #16). Keep the DEVICE CUU below equal to that build flag.

; -- interface: one point-to-point CTC (the M1 CTCI driver target) -----------
; DEVICE names the READ (lower/even) CUU; the driver takes write = cuu+1.
; 0500 read / 0501 write == the online Hercules CTCI pair (D U,,,500,4).
DEVICE  CTCA CTC 0500             ; CTC device at hardware address (cuu) 0500
LINK    LNK1 CTC 0 CTCA          ; IP link riding over device CTCA
HOME    192.168.200.1 LNK1       ; guest home addr (== tun0 peer on the host)
GATEWAY DEFAULTNET 192.168.200.2 LNK1 1500 0  ; default route via host tun0

; -- port reservations -------------------------------------------------------
PORT    23  TCP  TELNET          ; telnet reserved for jobname TELNET
PORT    21  TCP  FTPD            ; ftp control reserved for jobname FTPD

; -- protocol tuning ---------------------------------------------------------
TCPCONFIG RECVBUFRSIZE 16384 SENDBUFRSIZE 16384
UDPCONFIG UDPCHKSUM

; -- NSF extensions: buffer-pool sizing + startup trace ----------------------
; Pool names match the NSFMM/NSFBUF pools so NSFPOOL sizes them (spec 14.4).
NSFPOOL BUFSMALL 64              ; 64 small (256 B) packet buffers
NSFPOOL BUFLARGE 32             ; 32 large (2048 B) packet buffers
NSFTRACE CONFIG ON             ; trace the configuration component at startup
NSFTRACE DRIVER ON             ; trace the device driver (CTCI) for M1 bring-up
